name: peroxidase
classes: Acting on a peroxide as acceptor;
reaction: 2 phenolic donor + H2O2 = 2 phenoxyl radical of the donor + 2 H2O [RN:R03532]
comment: Heme proteins with histidine as proximal ligand. The iron in the resting enzyme is Fe(III). They also peroxidize non-phenolic substrates such as 3,3',5,5'-tetramethylbenzidine (TMB) and 2,2'-azinobis(3-ethylbenzthiazoline-6-sulfonic acid) (ABTS). Certain peroxidases (e.g. lactoperoxidase, SBP) oxidize bromide, iodide and thiocyanate.
